In this simulation, the voltage drop across the 560 $\Omega$ resistor \texttt{v(1,3)} turns out to be 10.26 volts, indicating a LED current of 18.32 mA by Ohm's Law (I=E/R).  R$_{1}$'s voltage drop (voltage between nodes 1 and 2) ends up being 11.15 volts, which across 100 k$\Omega$ gives a current of only 111.5 $\mu$A.  Obviously, a very small current is exerting control over a much larger current in this circuit.
 

 

